The paper deals with indoor scene synthesis, which is a computer vision problem, and specifically focuses on object selection and arrangement, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel approach based on a labeled LDA model, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also includes a user study, which suggests a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect. Finally, the paper deals with style constraints and multi-room settings, which could be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
